Notable Inhabitants.Individuals:
*[[Duke Folkwain]], Lord Woren's second in command. The Duke oversaw militia and Nimpeth's mercenary companies.
*[[Emanuel Foreister]], an adventuring [[rogue]] who survived horrors of the vanished mansion of the [[Centaur Bridge]] and retired to Nimpeth.
*[[Jhassala Lyrimmjakh]], a ship builder and a slaver hunter active in the late 15{{th}} century DR.{{Cite web/theedverse/2023-01-13 - Warship Builders}}
*[[Thoround]], the alchemist who discovered a magical use for blood and spittle of those afflicted by a strange forgetful disease that ravaged Vilhon Reach in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite polyhedron/55/The Everwinking Eye: A Closer Look at Maskyr's Eye|25}}
*[[Vogalsang]], a notorious slaver who held regular auctions in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
